## js interact with html
** use getElementById() to change html **
"""
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = "Hello JavaScript";
"""
## js where to 
** in HTML, js code must be inserted between <script> and </script> tags
"""
<script>
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = "My first Javascript";
</script>

## js functions and events
** a function can be called when an event occurs, like when the user click a button **
## js in <head> or <body>
## js can also be placed in external files:
"""
<script src="myScript.js"></script>
"""
## external references
"""
<script src="http://www.w3schools.com/js/myScript1.js"></script>
"""
## use a script located in a specific folder on the current web site:
"""
<script src="/js/myScript1.js"></script>
"""
### a script located in the same folder as the current page
"""
<script src="myScript1.js"></script>
"""

